annotationA: Integrin linked kinase (Ilk) is a pseudokinase that, together with stck and parvin, mediates part of the adhesive functions of integrins
annotationB: Icarus, isoform A; Icarus (Ics) encodes RSU1 (Ras suppressor 1), an adapter protein that participates in integrin-dependent processes by interacting with the integrin effector protein stck
